headline: CoreWeave, Archer Aviation, Carnival: Trending Tickers
summary: Wealth host Brad Smith and Catalysts co-host Madison Mills cover today's biggest market stories and trending tickers. CoreWeave (CRWV) surges after Nvidia (NVDA) reported an increased stake in the company. Archer Aviation (ACHR) jumps on news it will be the official air taxi provider for the 2028 Olympic Games in Los Angeles. Carnival (CCL) was upgraded to Hold from Reduce by HSBC analysts, citing strong booking trends. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Wealth here.

headline: HSBC lifts Carnival Corp. rating as it is now ‘in calmer waters’
summary: Investing.com -- HSBC raised its rating for Carnival (NYSE:CCL) Corp. to Hold from Reduce in a note to clients on Friday, citing resilient booking trends, improving profitability, and meaningful progress on debt reduction.

headline: CCL Stock Rises 29% in a Month: Should You Buy Now or Hold Steady?
